<section xml:id="sec-calcinmovies" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Calculus in the Movies</title>

  <p> Using infinitely close approximations displays power of calculus.
     Did you know that you can see calculus at work when you watch Finding Nemo? </p>

    <p>
      In fact Pixar Studios continually conducts rigorous mathematical research. 
      One of the mathematicians working for Pixar is Tony Rose, the first PhD in mathematics to win an Academy Award!
    </p>

